<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="178" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="25.[136,1452,1638,2061]" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,440,1638,1664]" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[440,465,1639,1664]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">—</emphasis>
The species has been found only inside a private property. 
<taxonomicName box="[1113,1375,1638,1664]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riocontensis">
<emphasis box="[1113,1375,1638,1664]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Bertolonia riocontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an AOO of 0 km², and should be classified as “Critically Endangered” (CR), following 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[1082,1232,1674,1700]" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories. Since it occurs only in one locality, it is not possible to estimate its Extent of Occurrence (EOO).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="179" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[136,1452,1638,2061]" lastBlockId="26.[136,1452,158,365]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="179" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1746,1772]" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[294,557,1746,1772]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riocontensis">
<emphasis box="[294,557,1746,1772]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Bertolonia riocontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[716,784,1746,1772]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in lowland rainforests, usually on rocky outcrops surrounded by forests on swampy areas (
<figureCitation box="[606,704,1782,1808]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[136,229,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[346,1239,435,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-140@19.[340,1247,425,1706]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A.Bertolonia linearifolia. B. Bertolonia maculata. C. Bertolonia marmorata. D. Bertolonia reginatoi. E. Bertolonia riocontensis. F. Bertolonia violacea. G. Bertolonia vitoriana." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597718/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Fig. 13e</figureCitation>
). It was collected with flowers in August, and fruits in August to September. It is recognized by the branches, petioles, leaf blades, hypanthium and sepals glandulose-punctate and also glandulose-villose (trichomes 
<quantity box="[531,667,1854,1881]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="2.2" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="0.9">0.9–3.5 mm</quantity>
long), thick stems (
<quantity box="[894,1004,1854,1881]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="5.0">5–12 mm</quantity>
wide), membranaceous and light green leaf blades with a markedly cordate base, and denticulate, densely ciliate margins. Furthermore, it has petals with an apiculate apex and stamens dehiscing through an extrorse pore. 
<taxonomicName box="[856,1120,1926,1952]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riocontensis">
<emphasis box="[856,1120,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">Bertolonia riocontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[1268,1403,1926,1952]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[1268,1403,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">B. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[136,297,1963,1988]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[136,297,1963,1988]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They all have branches, petioles, leaf blades, hypanthium and sepals glandulose-punctate and also glandulose-villose or glandulose-pilose (trichomes 
<quantity box="[719,835,1998,2025]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="2.45" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="0.9">0.9–4 mm</quantity>
long), ovate or widely ovate leaf blades with cordate bases, hypanthia with similar sizes (2.3–2.7 × 
<quantity box="[659,774,2034,2061]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.85" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="3.85" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.7">3.7–4 mm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[810,979,2035,2060]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riocontensis">
<emphasis box="[810,979,2035,2060]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">B. riocontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 2.4–3.1 × 
<quantity box="[1109,1224,2034,2061]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" unit="mm" value="3.35" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="3.0">3–3.7 mm</quantity>
in 
<emphasis box="[1260,1403,2034,2060]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="178">
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[1260,1399,2034,2060]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="25" pageNumber="178" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">B. maculata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 1.8–2.9 × 
<quantity box="[247,359,158,185]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.207" metricValueMax="6.35" metricValueMin="4.064" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" unit="in" value="2.05" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="1.6">1.6–2.5 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[364,520,159,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[364,520,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and petals with an apiculate apex. 
<taxonomicName box="[911,1174,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riocontensis">
<emphasis box="[911,1174,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">Bertolonia riocontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[1317,1451,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[1317,1451,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">B. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the leaf blades with denticulate and densely ciliate margins (
<emphasis box="[858,881,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">vs</emphasis>
. entire and moderately ciliate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[1257,1393,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[1257,1393,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">B. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and anthers dehiscing through an extrorse pore with non-thickened margins (
<emphasis box="[945,968,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">vs</emphasis>
. anthers dehiscing through an introrse pore with thickened margins). 
<taxonomicName box="[419,682,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="riocontensis">
<emphasis box="[419,682,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">Bertolonia riocontensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[827,983,267,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[827,983,267,292]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the leaf blades with an acuminate apex (
<emphasis box="[145,168,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">vs</emphasis>
. rounded or obtuse in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[433,593,303,328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[433,593,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and stamens dehiscing through an extrorse and rounded pore (
<emphasis box="[1331,1354,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">vs</emphasis>
. anthers dehiscing through an introrse and triangular pore). For more details see 
<bibRefCitation author="Bisewski, G. C. A. &amp; Bacci, L. &amp; Amorim, A. M. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[940,1188,338,364]" pageId="26" pageNumber="179" pagination="563 - 574" refId="ref18940" refString="Bisewski, G. C. A., Bacci, L. F, Amorim, A. M. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2020) Novelties in Bertolonia (Melastomataceae) from northeastern Brazil. Brazilian Journal of Botany 43 (3): 563 - 574. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 40415 - 020 - 00630 - 7" type="journal article" year="2020">
Bisewski 
<emphasis box="[1050,1106,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="179">et al.</emphasis>
(2020)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
